\name{trajfigR-package}
\alias{trajfigR-package}
\alias{trajfigR}
\title{NC-Style Trajectory Figure Toolkit}
\description{
Local R toolkit for NC-style trajectory figures from source-data tables.
}
\details{
The package is source-data-first and supports pseudotime maps, velocity arrows,
branch probability trends, gene trends, state-transition networks, and composite
trajectory figures. It depends on \pkg{ncfigR} for shared theme, layout, and export.
}
